          <h3>Bitcoin: A currency I can believe in</h3>

          <p>Back in early 2011 I read an article about Bitcoin. It immediately grabbed me as something special. Ravenously, I devoured all the
          information I could find about how it all worked. I read the <a href="http://bitcoin.org/bitcoin.pdf" target="">Satoshi paper</a> and was both reassured by its straightforward approach to the 
          problems of double-spend and impressed by the correct use of cryptography. I spent a lot of time following posts and discussion on the forums gathering more information about what could be done with it. I learned more about economics and international banking in that time than in all the years previously - a real eye opener.</p>

          <p>Over time I realised that what was missing was a merchant platform that would enable anyone, anywhere to start up their own
          business and for it to seamlessly link into other Bitcoin businesses, forming supply chains that spanned the globe. At the same time
          I discovered a whole raft of new and interesting web development technologies that I wanted to learn. Thus by writing a serious application dedicated to Bitcoin I could apply these technologies in a real world setting - a real win/win situation.</p>
          
          <p>You can read more about this process <a href="http://gary-rowe.com/agilestack/2012/06/06/multibit-merchant-genesis/" target="_blank">in my blog</a>.
        </div>

